title: Independent Candidate Tufail Anjum wins PK-55 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Tufail Anjum has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-55, Mardan-II by securing 41,084 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Adnan Khan who bagged 28,623 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 45.68 per cent.
